This paper deals with optimization problems and PDE-constrained problems, which are often solved using numerical methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses checkpointing, which is a technique used to reduce memory requirements in numerical computations. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper focuses on seismic applications, which could place it in cs.MS (Mathematical Software) or cs.SC (Scientific Computing).
